The House of Representatives yesterday urged the Federal Government to declare a state of emergency on unemployment and other challenges facing the Nigerian youths. The call was sequel to the adoption of a motion moved by Umar Muda Lawan (APC, Bauchi) and two others who said the youth were being faced by multiple challenges of unemployment and poverty. “If not addressed, it could undermine the stability and sustainable economic development of the country”. Declare emergency on unemployment, Senate orders Buhari High rate of illiteracy, unemployment in Bauchi worrisome - CSOs Buhari urged to declare state of emergency on youth unemployment